"state":{"raw_text":"Background:\nA mid-sized hospital group currently manages outpatient appointments through phone calls and spreadsheets. Patients often wait on hold for a long time, staff manually re-enter details into multiple systems, and appointment slots are sometimes double-booked or left unused because cancellations are not surfaced quickly.\n\nActors:\nPatients\nReception staff\nClinic managers\nDoctors\n\nProblem:\nThe hospital needs a digital appointment scheduling system that reduces call volume, makes it easier for patients to book or reschedule appointments, and gives staff better visibility into doctor availability.\n\nGoals:\nAllow patients to book, reschedule, and cancel appointments online.\nReduce manual work for reception staff.\nImprove appointment utilization by filling cancelled slots faster.\nProvide clinic managers with visibility into no-shows, cancellations, and schedule efficiency.\n\nFeatures:\nPatients should be able to search by specialty, location, and earliest available appointment.\nPatients should receive confirmation and reminder notifications by SMS or email.\nReception staff should be able to create bookings on behalf of patients.\nThe system should prevent double-booking of doctors and rooms.\nClinic managers should have a dashboard showing cancellations, no-shows, and utilization trends.\nHigh-priority patients should be flagged for faster scheduling when appropriate.\n\nConstraints:\nThe first release should support web only, not mobile apps.\nThe system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.\nIt must integrate with the hospital's existing patient record system.\nThe product should be usable by non-technical administrative staff with minimal training.\nReminder notifications should be configurable per clinic.","normalized_text":"Background:\nA mid-sized hospital group currently manages outpatient appointments through phone calls and spreadsheets. Patients often wait on hold for a long time, staff manually re-enter details into multiple systems, and appointment slots are sometimes double-booked or left unused because cancellations are not surfaced quickly.\n\nActors:\nPatients\nReception staff\nClinic managers\nDoctors\n\nProblem:\nThe hospital needs a digital appointment scheduling system that reduces call volume, makes it easier for patients to book or reschedule appointments, and gives staff better visibility into doctor availability.\n\nGoals:\nAllow patients to book, reschedule, and cancel appointments online.\nReduce manual work for reception staff.\nImprove appointment utilization by filling cancelled slots faster.\nProvide clinic managers with visibility into no-shows, cancellations, and schedule efficiency.\n\nFeatures:\nPatients should be able to search by specialty, location, and earliest available appointment.\nPatients should receive confirmation and reminder notifications by SMS or email.\nReception staff should be able to create bookings on behalf of patients.\nThe system should prevent double-booking of doctors and rooms.\nClinic managers should have a dashboard showing cancellations, no-shows, and utilization trends.\nHigh-priority patients should be flagged for faster scheduling when appropriate.\n\nConstraints:\nThe first release should support web only, not mobile apps.\nThe system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.\nIt must integrate with the hospital's existing patient record system.\nThe product should be usable by non-technical administrative staff with minimal training.\nReminder notifications should be configurable per clinic.","sections":["Background:\nA mid-sized hospital group currently manages outpatient appointments through phone calls and spreadsheets. Patients often wait on hold for a long time, staff manually re-enter details into multiple systems, and appointment slots are sometimes double-booked or left unused because cancellations are not surfaced quickly.","Actors:\nPatients\nReception staff\nClinic managers\nDoctors","Problem:\nThe hospital needs a digital appointment scheduling system that reduces call volume, makes it easier for patients to book or reschedule appointments, and gives staff better visibility into doctor availability.","Goals:\nAllow patients to book, reschedule, and cancel appointments online.\nReduce manual work for reception staff.\nImprove appointment utilization by filling cancelled slots faster.\nProvide clinic managers with visibility into no-shows, cancellations, and schedule efficiency.","Features:\nPatients should be able to search by specialty, location, and earliest available appointment.\nPatients should receive confirmation and reminder notifications by SMS or email.\nReception staff should be able to create bookings on behalf of patients.\nThe system should prevent double-booking of doctors and rooms.\nClinic managers should have a dashboard showing cancellations, no-shows, and utilization trends.\nHigh-priority patients should be flagged for faster scheduling when appropriate.","Constraints:\nThe first release should support web only, not mobile apps.\nThe system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.\nIt must integrate with the hospital's existing patient record system.\nThe product should be usable by non-technical administrative staff with minimal training.\nReminder notifications should be configurable per clinic."],"extracted_context":{"actors":["Patients","Reception staff","Clinic managers","Doctors"],"goals":["Allow patients to book, reschedule, and cancel appointments online.","Reduce manual work for reception staff.","Improve appointment utilization by filling cancelled slots faster.","Provide clinic managers with visibility into no-shows, cancellations, and schedule efficiency."],"features":["Patients should be able to search by specialty, location, and earliest available appointment.","Patients should receive confirmation and reminder notifications by SMS or email.","Reception staff should be able to create bookings on behalf of patients.","The system should prevent double-booking of doctors and rooms.","Clinic managers should have a dashboard showing cancellations, no-shows, and utilization trends.","High-priority patients should be flagged for faster scheduling when appropriate."],"constraints":["The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","It must integrate with the hospital's existing patient record system.","The product should be usable by non-technical administrative staff with minimal training.","Reminder notifications should be configurable per clinic."]},"epics":[{"title":"Online Appointment Booking","summary":"Allow patients to book, reschedule, and cancel appointments online.","stories":[{"title":"Search by Specialty, Location, and Earliest Available Appointment","story":"As a patient, I want to be able to search for doctors by specialty, location, and earliest available appointment, so that I can find the best fit for my needs.","acceptance_criteria":[{"text":"Given a valid search query is submitted, when the service processes the request, then the search results are displayed with relevant information."},{"text":"Given the user selects a doctor from the search results, when the appointment booking process begins, then the system displays available time slots for the selected doctor."}],"dependencies":[{"name":"The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","dependency_type":"depends_on"},{"name":"The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","dependency_type":"depends_on"}]},{"title":"Confirmation and Reminder Notifications","story":"As a patient, I want to receive confirmation and reminder notifications by SMS or email, so that I don't forget my appointments.","acceptance_criteria":[{"text":"Given the user books an appointment, when the system sends a confirmation notification, then the notification is received by the user within a reasonable time frame."},{"text":"Given the user has opted for reminder notifications, when the appointment approaches, then the system sends a reminder notification to the user."}],"dependencies":[{"name":"The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","dependency_type":"depends_on"},{"name":"The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","dependency_type":"depends_on"}]}]},{"title":"Reception Staff Efficiency","summary":"Reduce manual work for reception staff.","stories":[{"title":"Create Bookings on Behalf of Patients","story":"As a reception staff, I want to be able to create bookings on behalf of patients, so that I can streamline the booking process.","acceptance_criteria":[{"text":"Given a valid patient record is submitted, when the reception staff creates a new booking, then the system updates the patient's schedule accordingly."},{"text":"Given the user attempts to create a duplicate booking, when the system detects the error, then it prevents the duplicate booking and notifies the user."}],"dependencies":[{"name":"The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","dependency_type":"depends_on"},{"name":"The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","dependency_type":"depends_on"}]},{"title":"Prevent Double-Booking of Doctors and Rooms","story":"As a reception staff, I want the system to prevent double-booking of doctors and rooms, so that we avoid scheduling conflicts.","acceptance_criteria":[{"text":"Given multiple bookings attempt to schedule for the same time slot, when the system detects the conflict, then it prevents the duplicate booking and notifies the user."},{"text":"Given a valid new booking is submitted, when the system updates the schedule, then it ensures that no conflicts arise with existing bookings."}],"dependencies":[{"name":"The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","dependency_type":"depends_on"},{"name":"The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","dependency_type":"depends_on"}]}]},{"title":"Clinic Manager Insights","summary":"Improve appointment utilization by filling cancelled slots faster.","stories":[{"title":"Dashboard for Cancellations, No-Shows, and Utilization Trends","story":"As a clinic manager, I want to have a dashboard showing cancellations, no-shows, and utilization trends, so that I can make data-driven decisions.","acceptance_criteria":[{"text":"Given the user accesses the dashboard, when the system displays relevant metrics, then the metrics are accurate and up-to-date."},{"text":"Given the user attempts to view historical data, when the system retrieves the data, then it presents a clear and concise visualization of the trends."}],"dependencies":[{"name":"The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","dependency_type":"depends_on"},{"name":"The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","dependency_type":"depends_on"}]},{"title":"Flag High-Priority Patients for Faster Scheduling","story":"As a clinic manager, I want high-priority patients to be flagged for faster scheduling when appropriate, so that we can prioritize their needs.","acceptance_criteria":[{"text":"Given the user flags a patient as high-priority, when the system updates the schedule, then it ensures that the priority is reflected in the booking process."},{"text":"Given multiple patients attempt to book at the same time, when the system detects the conflict, then it prioritizes the high-priority patient and notifies the user."}],"dependencies":[{"name":"The first release should support web only, not mobile apps.","dependency_type":"depends_on"},{"name":"The system must comply with healthcare privacy requirements.","dependency_type":"depends_on"}]}]}],"open_questions":["Which stories should be prioritized for the first implementation slice?"],"assumptions":["The listed features are all in scope for the initial backlog draft.","The extracted goals accurately represent the business outcome."],"summary":"Generated 6 rough user stories for Patients, Reception staff, covering 6 key feature areas."}}% 